1️⃣ Download & Prepare
•	Download the project folder flask_crud_api.zip and unzip it to your computer.

2️⃣ Open Terminal
•	Open VS Code terminal or Command Prompt.
•	Navigate to the project folder:
cd "C:\path\to\flask_crud_api"
Replace "C:\path\to\" with your actual folder location.

3️⃣ (Optional) Create Virtual Environment
•	Recommended to avoid conflicts with other Python packages:
python -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\activate
•	Terminal should show (venv) at the start.
•	If PowerShell blocks activation:
Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser
.\venv\Scripts\activate

4️⃣ Install Dependencies
•	Install all required packages using pip:
pip install -r requirements.txt
•	This installs Flask, Flask-RESTful, and Flask-SQLAlchemy.

5️⃣ Run the Flask API
•	Start the server:
python app.py
•	The server will run at:
http://127.0.0.1:5000/

6️⃣ Test Endpoints
You can test the API endpoints using Postman, curl, or any REST client.
Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/items	Create a new item
GET	/items	Get all items
GET	/items/<id>	Get single item by ID
PUT	/items/<id>	Update item by ID
DELETE	/items/<id>	Delete item by ID
Example curl commands:
# Create item
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name":"Book","description":"Python Book"}' http://127.0.0.1:5000/items

# Get all items
curl http://127.0.0.1:5000/items

# Update item
curl -X PUT -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name":"Notebook"}' http://127.0.0.1:5000/items/1

# Delete item
curl -X DELETE http://127.0.0.1:5000/items/1

7️⃣ Stop the Server
•	When finished, press CTRL + C in the terminal to stop the Flask server.

8️⃣ Notes
•	Always run python app.py from the terminal, not inside the Python >>> prompt.
•	Using a virtual environment is optional but recommended to avoid dependency conflicts.
•	You can view all items, create, update, or delete items using Postman or curl commands.

